extends ../base

block content
  p In the early 90's Gillette started posting free shaving kits to men to celebrate their 18th birthday.
  p The idea was simple —!{' '}
    span.italic Hook men at the age they decide their shaving brand for life.
  img(src="https://ik.imagekit.io/o08ysq9vx/newsletters/nl5/nl2b.jpg" alt="Gilette's 18th birthday shaving kits").img__100
  p Let's do some rough maths:
  p.inwardSpeech 90% of men pay no attention. 10% get hooked on Gillette. And spend $40/yr on replacement blades for the next 10 years.
  p.inwardSpeech That's an average return of!{' '}
    span.bold $40
    |!{' '}(10% * $40 * 10 yrs). On a gift that costs $10 to post.
  p Gillette post two million a year. $80M revenue. $60M profit.
  p.inwardSpeech “Give 'em the razor, sell 'em the blades”. — King Camp Gillette
  img(src="https://ik.imagekit.io/o08ysq9vx/newsletters/nl5/nl2q.png" alt="Gilette's free shaving kits marketing").img__100
  p
    span.italic Thanks for reading — Harry